parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive brake noise and squealing can be a sign of worn-out brake pads or a faulty brake system, which can lead to reduced braking performance and increased stopping distances, potentially causing accidents.

especially when reversing or slowing down; brake dust on wheels.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake performance issues can cause the vehicle to take longer to stop or jerk to a stop, potentially leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy; brakes take longer to stop the vehicle; vehicle jerks to a stop; brake pedal goes to the floor with no braking occurring.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive brake dust and pad wear can lead to reduced braking performance and increased stopping distances, potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Excessive brake dust on wheels; brake pads wear out quickly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The adaptive cruise control issues can cause the vehicle to accelerate or decelerate unexpectedly, potentially leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Adaptive cruise control accelerates or decelerates unexpectedly; system acts on its own and may exceed the set speed limit.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door check arm/hinge can cause the door to not open or close properly, leading to difficulties in entering or exiting the vehicle, and potentially causing accidents or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of spot welds can cause structural issues with the door, leading to difficulties in opening or closing the door, and potentially causing accidents or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear hatch/liftgate can cause the hatch to open or close unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.

hatch does not stay open

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the paint and body panels can cause cosmetic issues and potentially lead to structural problems.

paint discoloration

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The presence of sharp metal edges can cause injuries to occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design of the dashboard trim can cause distractions while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
